Add image open/download link on Markdown pages. This is surprisingly fiddly,
because the image is in-lined without a specific link, so there's no link to
click, as there is with links in Gemtext documents.

Improve accuracy of emoji detection. 

Implement caching (but how, given the lack of timestamp?)

Find a way to indicate when page rendering is ongoing, and when it is complete.
It's not usually a problem for text pages, but images sometimes take a while to
transfer.

Do something with un-actionable links like "about:xxx" and "gopher:xxx" -- may
be impossible without re-implementing the viewer completely.

Catch redirect loops.

Add support for Spartan, Nex, maybe Gopher.

Implement a download manager. At least, find a way to prevent the program exiting whilst a 
download is in progress.

Zoom/Scale (very difficult, without reimplementing HTMLEditorKit).

Add bookmark support.

